iata is a plant in the family Malvaceae, native to southern Europe. It is an upright perennial herb, typically growing 1-2 meters tall and 1 meter wide, with a single stem and a large, cupped rosette of leaves at its base. The leaves are 20-60 centimeters long and 10-30 centimeters wide, with 3-5 lobes and a serrated margin. The plant produces pink to white flowers in late spring and early summer, with 5 petals and a prominent, hairy calyx. The fruit is a capsule, containing numerous small seeds, and is 10-20 centimeters long and 5-10 centimeters wide."}